  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVID-19 Response in Hajjah</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Wells rehabilitation in Hajjah. Oxfam will target 7 open dug wells in Mabian district. This intervention will benefit from it 717 HHs. Quick assessment confirmed that people in this area collect water from the 7 dug wells for drinking water which considered as contaminated water. In addition, collecting water is a tough job for women and girls as they have to walk more than 2 km to the water source. The intervention need will include excavation and filling around of well  Paving stone; Supply and build solid concrete block to increase the wall of dug well installed  steel/fibber cover; construction of basin for animals drinking; cleaning and chlorination from contamination. Rehabilitate of these sources will reduce the risk of infection and the spread of the COVID -19 as well as other water borne diseases related to water pollution, acute watery diarrhea and cholera.</narrative>
  </description>
